# Normalize line endings to LF in both the repository and the working tree.
#
# This project is developed on Linux / WSL. Editing through the Windows
# filesystem layer was rewriting files with CRLF, which made `git status`
# show every file as modified (a whole-tree line-ending diff) even when only
# a few lines actually changed. Forcing LF ends that churn.
#
# `text=auto` lets Git auto-detect text vs binary, so genuinely binary files
# are never touched; `eol=lf` pins the working-tree ending to LF regardless of
# core.autocrlf on the machine.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Belt-and-suspenders: never normalize known-binary assets.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.ico  binary
